00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:08,480
and your reflections on that.

304
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:12,650
Yeah, so this is a
program that we--

305
00:16:12,650 --> 00:16:17,660
I mean, it's one of the
things that I've done at MIT--

306
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:19,380
maybe one of the
top three things.

307
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:22,400
And I don't even know what the
other two are, that I'm, A,

308
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:25,760
the happiest I have done and
the most proud I have done

309
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:29,810
and the most grateful
that that possibility was

310
00:16:29,810 --> 00:16:34,738
offered to me, because,
frankly, it was a bit of--

311
00:16:34,738 --> 00:16:38,080
we were all learning.

312
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:42,910
Open Learning people, from
engineers to leadership,

313
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:44,950
and us at the same
time, when we were

